      "writtenOn": "2026-04-01T05:46:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I understand correctly, this bazel sync invocation was originally added as a workaround to prefetch the npm repositories for PolyGerrit.\n\nThere is no direct Bazel 9 replacement for bazel sync. With bzlmod, external repositories are resolved and fetched automatically as needed during build / test.\n\nSo this command is obsolete now. In fact, after the PolyGerrit migration to rules_nodejs 6 and bzlmod (change 520342), we no longer need this explicit prefetch step.",
      "parentUuid": "9e60eba8_d5c64f03",
      "revId": "6c5ce1535a470505e17b4b9b9c360ba2cb8bbd6b",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
